The paper deals with the detection of nonlinearly distorted OFDM signals, which is a problem in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed receiver in frequency-selective multipath channels, which falls under the category of cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The use of the generalized approximate message passing (GAMP) framework suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.SP (Signal Processing). The proposed receiver can be implemented in software or hardware, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with the detection of nonlinearly distorted signals, which is a problem in control systems, suggesting that it may also belong to the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
